sais graduate admissions student affairs student affairs information services applications tools & technology support projects & plans policies & standards stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit graduate admissions graduate admissions student affairs information systems information stanford universal faculty staff perennial applyyourself a product provided by hobsons is an online application software tool the registrar's office and the graduate school of business currently use applyyourself to manage their applications from applicants seeking admission to regular graduate and gsb phd programs for these purposes stanford has used applyyourself to process applications from students around the world using applyyours elf applicants present all of their admission information online and indicate their recommenders see plans to replace applyyourself below applyyourself is not used by all stanford academic programs the undergraduate admissions office uses the hobsons common application online system the stanford law school and the stanford school of medicine use separate systems geared to the legal and medical professions all graduate admission information however eventually makes its way into peoplesoft student administration axess once students are admitted and accept their offer from stanford their application information is used to activate them as students in peoplesoft they are then eligible to enroll and participate in the world of academic activities they will encounter at stanford a new project spearheaded by the registrar's office and the gsb phd program and which includes faculty and staff from several departments will result in the replacement of the applyyourself system with collegenet's applyweb system building on our success in working in partnership with collegenet a new system will go live in august 2010 this will introduce the ability of departments to evaluate and rank applicants online a capability they have not had before groups 